'''Gregg-Wallace Farm Tenant House''' is a historic home located near [[Mars Bluff, South Carolina|Mars Bluff]], [[Florence County, South Carolina]].  It was built about 1890, and is representative of a typical Mars Bluff vernacular tenant house for African Americans. Tenant houses often evolved from one-room slave houses, first by the addition of a shed room at the rear and a front porch, then by the addition of a second room.<ref name = nrhpinv>{{Cite web | author = Amelia Wallace Vernon | title =Gregg-Wallace Farm Tenant House | work = National Register of Historic Places - Nomination and Inventory | date = August 2001 | url = http://www.nationalregister.sc.gov/florence/S10817721008/S10817721008.pdf | format = pdf | accessdate = 5 July 2012}}</ref><ref name = scdah>{{Cite web | title =Gregg-Wallace Farm Tenant House, Florence County (310 Price Rd., Mars Bluff vicinity)| work = National Register Properties in South Carolina | publisher = South Carolina Department of Archives and History  | url = http://www.nationalregister.sc.gov/florence/S10817721008/index.htm | accessdate = 5 July 2012}}</ref>

It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2002.<ref name = nris/>

